### CSS Variables Template
Every style MUST define these CSS variables at `:root`:
```css
:root {
  --bg: #...; --surface: #...; --primary: #...;
  --accent: #...; --text: #...; --text-muted: #...;
  --border: #...; --shadow: rgba(...);
}
```

### Style-Specific Implementation Notes

### glass (Glassmorphism)
```css
backdrop-filter: blur(20px); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); border-radius: 16px;
```

### hacker (Dark Hacker)
```css
font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
background: #0a0a0a; color: #00ff41;
text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,255,65,0.3);
```

### luxury (Luxury/Refined)
```css
font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
background: #1a1a2e; color: #e8d5b7;
letter-spacing: 0.05em;
```

### neo (Neomorphism)
```css
background: #e0e5ec;
box-shadow: 8px 8px 16px #b8bec7, -8px -8px 16px #ffffff;
border-radius: 12px;
```

### pastel (Soft/Pastel)
```css
background: #fef7f0; color: #5a4a42;
border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);
```

Match implementation complexity to the vision. Maximalist needs elaborate code. Minimalist needs restraint and precision.
